  </table>

  <p>Notice an important pattern: the jump from N3 to N2 is the steepest. You need 350 more kanji and 2,250 more vocabulary words. Many learners plateau at this stage, which is why N3-to-N2 typically takes the longest per-level study period. Planning for this difficulty spike prevents frustration and burnout.</p>

